<div class="page-header"><h3>General Functionality</h3><hr class="notop"></div><ol><li><div id="find_total_dots"><h4>How to find number of dots from string using Javascript?   </h4>Following code Find number of dots from string using javascript.<br/>By using this function we can get the no of repeated character from the string using java script. <br/><strong>Download Source File :</strong> <a href="download/find_total_dots_ex.rar" >SRC Files</a><h6>File Name :script.js </h6><pre class="prettyprint linenums"><code class="language-js">function count(s1, letter) {    return s1.match( new RegExp(letter,'g') ).length; }</code>	</pre><strong>Example 1: </strong><br/>We can test email address by above function like :This function return boolean value , it will return either true or false based on the validation test.If user has supplied wrong email address then it  will return false otherwise return true. <pre class="prettyprint linenums"><code class="language-js">	count('Yes. I want. to. place a. lot of. dots.','\\.'); 	//=> output : 6</code>	</pre><strong>Example 2: </strong><br/>We can test email address by above function like :This function return boolean value , it will return either true or false based on the validation test.If user has supplied wrong email address then it  will return false otherwise return true. <pre class="prettyprint linenums"><code class="language-js">	count('2....3','\\.'); 	//=> output : 4</code>	</pre></div></li></ol>